# BLAKE3-256 pins for cloister/confinement/v1 canonical manifests.
#
# Distinct from VECTORS.sha256 (which is a SHA-256 CONTENT INTEGRITY pin
# via the sha256sum convention). This file pins the BLAKE3-256
# `confinementDigest` per README §7 — the identity-committed digest a
# substrate runner computes at bundle-start time and cross-checks against
# the workload identity's cert extension.
#
# The line shape mirrors `sha256sum` (`<64-hex>  <path>`) so the same
# parser handles both files. Verified by
# `tests/verify_confinement_digest.rs` (bead ley-line-open-193170).
#
# Cross-impl conformance history:
# - cloister computed this value via leyline-cas-ffi (Σ substrate hash)
# - LLO computes it via the `blake3` crate directly in this test
# Byte-identical result → the ContentAddressed impl on `[u8]`
# (`Hash(*blake3::hash(self).as_bytes())` in leyline-core/substrate.rs)
# and the direct blake3 crate compute the same digest for the same bytes.

